ch 1989|accessdate=15 April 2013 |author=IWM}}\n:[[Lorne Welch]] was a British NCO flying instructor in GB, 1938\u20131942; officer with 25 Operation Training Unit, RAF in GB, 1942; POW at Stalag Luft III, Sagan and Oflag IV C, Colditz in Germany, 1943\u20131945\n* {{cite web |url=http://www.iwm.org.uk/collections/item/object/80027793 |title=recording [Colditz Society/Dominic Bruce]|work=IWM Collections Search|date=January 2006|accessdate=15 April 2013 |author=IWM}}\n:Dominic Bruce served as navigator with Bomber Command, 1939\u20131941; POW in Spangenburg Castle and Oflag IV C, Colditz in Germany, 1941\u20131945\nFrom all IWM collections:\n* {{cite web |url=http://www.iwm.org.uk/collections/search?query=colditz&items_per_page=50 |title=Collections Search for \"colditz\" |accessdate=15 April 2013 |author=IWM}}\n* {{cite web |url=http://www.iwm.org.uk/collections/search?query=oflag+iv&submit=&items_per_page=50|title=Collections Search for \"oflag iv\" |accessdate=15 April 2013 |author=IWM}}\n\n===Prisoner obituaries===\n* James de Deane Yule: September 17, 1916 \u2013 December 25, 2000 \u2013 [http://www.mishalov.com/Yule.html obituary]\n* [[John William Best]]: 1913 \u2013 April 22, 2000 \u2014 [http://www.mishalov.com/Best.html John William Best]\n* [[Dominic Bruce]]: June 7, 1915 \u2013 February 12, 2000 \u2014 [http://www.mishalov.com/Bruce.html obituary]\n* [[Hugh Bruce]]: January 26, 1919 \u2013 January 9, 2003 \u2014 [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/1419707/Major-Hugh-Bruce.html obituary]\n* James Hugh Cecil (Jim) Chesshire: December 28, 1916 \u2013 October, 2000 \u2014 [http://www.mishalov.com/Chesshire.html obituary]\n* [[Hugo Ironside]]: June 14, 1918 \u2013 October 3, 2008 \u2014 [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/3550917/Brigadier-Hugo-Ironside.html obituary]\n* Douggie Moir: August 24, 1918 \u2013 May 6, 2008 \u2014 [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/1942625/Lieutenant-Colonel-Douggie-Moir.html obituary]\n* [[Francis Steinmetz]]: 20 September 1914 \u2013 2 January 2006 \u2014 [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/1511392/Kapitein-Luitenant-Francis-Steinmetz.html obituary]\n* [[Pete Tunstall]]: 1 December 1918 \u2013 27 July 2013 \u2014 [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/10209913/Squadron-Leader-Peter-Tunstall.html obituary]\n* [[Lorne Welch|Patrick Palles Lorne Elphinstone Welch]]: 12 August 1916 \u2013 15 May 1998 \u2014 [http://www.times-archive.co.uk/news/pages/tim/98/06/01/timobiobi02004.html obituary]\n\n{{Colditz}}\n{{Main German WWII POW camps 1944-1945}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Oflag Iv-C}}\n[[Category:Oflags]]\n[[Category:Colditz Castle]]\n", "name_user": "Littlewing44", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oflag_IV-C"}
